text:
Bayside Ave., at the S.E. corner of Union Street, showing in two views, looking southeast, the Mitchell house which remained in the family from 1804 to 1921. This is a set of two views.

April 1925.

folder: Union Street & Bayside Avenue, Queens, NY
text:
Union Street (Whitestone Ave.) (right), south from about Twenty-ninth Ave. The house seen in this view faces Bayside Ave. This site was the headquarters and the property of Col. Hamilton of the British army. The house that then stood on the site burned down in 1779. The present house was erected in 1780. Henry Mitchell purchased it in 1804 and it was not sold again until 1921. This is a set of three views. No. 2 shows a close up of the house at the corner while No. 3 shows it on Bayside Ave.

April 1925.
Views 1 & 2.
View No. 3: 1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

folder: Union Street & Bayside Avenue, Queens, NY
text:
Union Street (Whitestone Ave.), north of Thirty-second Ave., showing the Mitchell house at the S.E. corner of Union Street and Bayside Ave., in a set of four views. Some of the owners of this establishment were Col. Archibald Hamilton, John Hoagland, Henry T. Mitchell in 1860, and the Wm. Mitchell Estate in 1873. Alice, wife of Col. Hamilton and granddaughter of Lt. Gov Colden died in January 1781. This house was erected in 1780.

1922.
Views 1 & 4.
View 2: July 1923.
View 4: About 1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
